description: A wave of fear washes across Gotham City as a mysterious toxin radically alters the bodies of its criminals, sending crazed villains into the streets and stretching the resources of the police department. Can Batman and his vigilante partners follow the clues and uncover the perpetrator's real identity? And when one fabled hero is stricken by the poison, the trail will point to the mysterious White Rabbit.
name: Catch Me If You Can

description: Continued from G.I. Romances, 22 is the first issue as Exotic Romances

No one is safe now that Batman's discovered the connection between Mayor Sharp and Hugo Strange! Commissioner Gordon sees that his "traditional" methods aren't getting him anywhere... and Batman will have to look elsewhere for help. But just as Strange thinks he has the upper hand in capturing Batman, we learn that once again, Batman's ahead of the game--with the help of some old friends.
name: Observations (Part 3)

Meet Mary Specter, a misunderstood teenage girl trained to be a lucid dreamer. Mary's father runs a sleep disorder clinic where Mary enters the ghastly dreams of severely disturbed people in an attempt to help them. When a patient is revealed to be a serial killer, the nightmare world and the waking one become intertwined, putting Mary in real jeopardy. Set in a world where the boundaries between dreams and reality are tenuous, Night Mary, courtesy of Rick Remender and Kieron Dwyer (Remains), is a very dark and terrifying trip into psychological horror.

Lanterns united! Green, yellow, red, blue soldiers from every Lantern Corps stand shoulder-to-shoulder against an unthinkable enemy: the Guardians of Oa! It's the New Guardians vs. old in a battle that will forever change Kyle Rayner's standing in the Green Lantern Corps! Plus: If the lone Orange Lantern ring is with Kyle Rayner, then what happened to its owner, Larfleeze? Finally, the answer revealed!
name: Part Three

description:
'FOREVER' Part One THIS IS IT! The 50th anniversary issue of the Fantastic Four! This month we begin the 5-part conclusion to the story that began over 30 issues ago. Joins us for the epic celebration of Marvel's First Family with 96 pages of all-new content written by Jonathan Hickman with art by Steve Epting, Carmine Di Giandomenico, Leinil Yu and Farel Dalrymple.

Note: The series ended with issue 588 and was replaced with a new comic named " FF" (or Future Foundation) for 11 issues before returning to the Fantastic Four title with issue 600.
name: Forever, Part 1

Conrad "Connie" Bremen is an ex-con carrying the stench of a sordid, secret past. Connie just wants to get on with his life, but he's attracting the attention of all the wrong people: the Mob, the CIA, the FBI -- and the nymphomaniac daughter of a Texas millionaire. Everyone has plans for Connie, whether he likes it or not. And some of those plans include the murder of a president. True assassins are made, not born. For Connie Bremen the road to Dallas begins and ends here, in the Badlands.

Introduction by Frank Miller.

The ultimate adventure tale of a bygone age, when pyrates ruled the waters! Beginning with his childhood through to his bitter end, Blackbeard's legacy has never been explored as deeply and illustrated as beautifully by Mario Guevara than now! Also contains biographical information on Blackbeard and a complete cover gallery.
name: TPB

description:
A secret amongst the Druids

A mysterious Lady of the woods.

A young king-to-be.

A compelling saga entrenched in the mythos of Arthur.

An entirely fictional twist that tells a tale from young Arthurs foster age with Sir Ector, before he became king. Fifteen is a difficult age for anyone and that includes the young Arthur. While all the knights do the fighting and reveling, Arthur wearies of the day-to-day duties of being squire to his brother Kay. When a beautiful noblewoman comes to the manor requiring his assistance, Arthur is eager to accompany her, and as they walk the same path, the lady enlightens Arthur on how to be insightful and look within himself, however her own life has been a tragic one. It seems that Saxons and dark druids conspire against this mysterious and enchanted lady. This narrative is a lesson learned early for the king-to-be of all Britain.

Chastised for causing the death of Lancelots betrothed, Balin desires to return to the graces of the Round Table and Arthur gives him the opportunity. Balin delivers a pledge to a dying knight that he will pick up the cause of Lady Ceri and then finds himself battling an invisible knight. Can a magical artifact save him?

volume.name: Legends of Camelot: Sir Balin and the Dolorous Stroke

description:
In the days of the great king, Uther, there was another good, but lesser King. A man named Gereint. He was wed to his love, the Lady Enid who was much younger than he. His love for her was so great, that he spent his days with thoughts of only cherishing her and abandoned his adventure and noble actions.

Now he ventured out to prove not only himself, but to prove how strong the love of his was with Enid. Would he ride against an unbeatable foe to prove his worthto prove his rightful place on the throneto prove he deserved the Lady Enids love?

An enchanting tale deep in the past of King Arthur.

volume.name: Legends of Camelot: Quest for Honor

description:
The most famous magician in myth or history.

The mage who guided a great king.

He was Merlin.

Delving deep into the mythos of King Arthur, this issue tells the tale of a young Merlin-called Myrddin and his mysterious beginnings. It shows how he came to ambiguously prophesy a future for the land of Britain. Living in Carmarthen with his mother, the men of King Vortigern come to seize the "fatherless child" whose blood is needed for a sacrifice so that Vortigerns stronghold against the High Kings sons can be completed without incident. But Myrddin, while in a trance, has a pointed way of convincing him that he knows more than the kings own druid. Will Myrddins predictions come to pass?

The DARKWING DUCK/DUCKTALES crossover 20 years in the making is finally here! Somewhere in the shadows, a manipulative force has spread chaos throughout the cities of Duckburg and St. Canard and it's caught the attention of their two most famous residents, the trailblazing tycoon Scrooge McDuck and the daring do-gooder Darkwing Duck! Can these two larger-than-life luminaries work together to discover the source of the mayhem, or will all be lost in the pursuit of Dangerous Currency? Its the end of an era as we say our last goodbye to Disney at KABOOM! Dont miss this landmark final trade paperback collection from the relationship that put kids comics back on the map!
name: Dangerous Currency
